1
00:00:03,578 --> 00:00:09,732
No less than Śrīmatī Rādhāṛāṇī Herself,
in the Brahmar-gīta,

2
00:00:09,785 --> 00:00:16,349
in Her divine madness She says …

3
00:00:16,626 --> 00:00:19,263
Theyr'e speaking of Kṛṣṇa addiction—

4
00:00:19,263 --> 00:00:22,308
[Krishna Addiction]

5
00:00:23,031 --> 00:00:28,775
addicted to speaking about Kṛṣṇa,
to hearing about Kṛṣṇa—

6
00:00:29,739 --> 00:00:34,244
and She says,
“Yad-anucharita-līlā-karṇa-pīyūṣa-vipruṭ-

7
00:00:34,244 --> 00:00:45,127
sakṛd-adana-vidhūta-dvandva-dharmā vinaṣṭāḥ
sapadi gṛha-kuṭumbaṁ dīnam utsṛjya dīnā

8
00:00:45,127 --> 00:00:53,656
bahava iha vihaṅgā bhikṣu-charyāṁ charanti.”
[SB: 10.47.18]

9
00:00:56,240 --> 00:01:00,990
She says, “Yad-anucharita-līlā-
karṇa-pīyūṣa-vipruṭ;

10
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:07,157
hearing about Kṛṣṇa,” She said,
“what happens is, in this hearing …”

11
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:12,557
(We’re talking about being 
a conscious being: hearing, being aware.)

12
00:01:12,557 --> 00:01:16,501
She’s saying, “If you put
your consciousness to this,

13
00:01:16,501 --> 00:01:20,532
if in your consciousness 
Kṛṣṇa conception enters,

14
00:01:20,532 --> 00:01:22,651
then what it does, it …

15
00:01:22,651 --> 00:01:28,827
a drop of this nectar
lands on the heart.”

16
00:01:29,780 --> 00:01:32,826
One drop touches the heart.

17
00:01:32,858 --> 00:01:37,144
One drop of hearing Kṛṣṇa nectar
touches the heart.

18
00:01:37,144 --> 00:01:40,266
Like Kṛṣṇa-karṇamṛta.

19
00:01:40,483 --> 00:01:44,200
That’s what it means,
‘Kṛṣṇa nectar for the ear’.

20
00:01:44,696 --> 00:01:46,195
One drop touches the heart,

21
00:01:46,195 --> 00:01:49,702
and She's saying,
“Then, it dissolves everything.”

22
00:01:49,702 --> 00:01:52,890
One drop. It dissolves all attachment.

23
00:01:52,890 --> 00:01:56,428
“Vidhuta-dvandva-dharma vinashtah.”
Finished.

24
00:01:56,428 --> 00:02:01,701
All attachment will be finished
by one drop of hearing about Kṛṣṇa.

25
00:02:02,141 --> 00:02:07,169
And Guru Mahārāj told the example

26
00:02:07,353 --> 00:02:11,506
of when they—sometimes for safes,

27
00:02:11,783 --> 00:02:16,274
the thieves, when they
want to open a safe …

28
00:02:16,459 --> 00:02:19,050
You can try with a combination
this way, that way,

29
00:02:19,113 --> 00:02:21,889
but they would take
this type of, like,

30
00:02:21,889 --> 00:02:24,287
a drop of some kind
of acid or something,

31
00:02:24,287 --> 00:02:26,805
they put that, and it burns 
a hole through the metal,

32
00:02:26,805 --> 00:02:30,797
and then everything opens.

33
00:02:30,797 --> 00:02:34,309
He’s saying something like that.

34
00:02:34,407 --> 00:02:37,692
One drop of this substance
is so powerful

35
00:02:37,692 --> 00:02:41,754
that we'll finish with all illusion
and all attachment,

36
00:02:41,856 --> 00:02:44,447
worldly attachments, etc.

37
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Subtitles by the Amara.org community

